Package: RsparkleR
Type: Package
Title: RsparkleR provides an R interface for launching virtual machines and deploying Sparkler
Version: 0.1.0
Author: c( person("Vincent", "Terrasi", email = "vincent@data-seo.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
            person("Mark", "Edmondson", email = "r@sunholo.com", role = c("aut", "cre")) ))
Maintainer: Vincent Terrasi <vincent@data-seo.com>
URL: https://github.com/voltek62/RsparkleR
BugReports: https://github.com/voltek62/RsparkleR/issues
Description: Interact with the OVH API in R. Lets you create, start and stop instances with Sparkler.
  Sparkler (contraction of Spark-Crawler) is a new web crawler that makes use of recent advancements in distributed computing and information retrieval domains by conglomerating various Apache projects like Spark, Kafka, Lucene/Solr, Tika, and Felix.
License: GPL (>= 3)
Depends:
    R (>= 3.3.0)
Imports:
    reticulate (>= 1.3.0),
    jsonlite (>= 1.1),
    dplyr (>= 0.7)
Suggests:
    devtools (>= 1.12.0),
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    testthat
LazyData: TRUE
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
